The paper introduces a new discrepancy score between two distributions and develops hypothesis testing procedures to test if two data sets come from similar distributions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Statistics Theory (cs.ST), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on distribution similarity and hypothesis testing, Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) seem to be the most likely sub-categories.
